SEO for indexable routes

When adding or editing a public, indexable route (page.tsx / parent layout.tsx with generateMetadata), check whether it already matches the optimizations used on /welcome and /contact. If anything is missing, apply the same pattern—do not ship a weaker SEO surface for new pages.

Required when missing

generateMetadata with locale-aware title and description (via getTranslations and message keys, not hard-coded English only).
keywords: comma-separated string in messages (e.g. *.seo.keywords), parsed with parseSeoKeywords from @/lib/seo/parse-keywords.utils, and passed to metadata.
alternates.canonical and alternates.languages via getCanonicalUrl + getAlternateLanguages for that route path.
robots: { index: true, follow: true } when the page should be indexed (adjust only if intentionally noindex).
Open Graph + Twitter: use buildOpenGraphAndTwitter from @/lib/seo/build-page-social-metadata.utils so url, locale, alternateLocale, images, and Twitter card stay consistent.
JSON-LD: add SeoPageJsonLd (or extend StructuredData / shared schema only when appropriate) so the page has structured data aligned with its purpose; keep scripts as inline application/ld+json in server components (see seo-page-jsonld), not next/script.

Messages

Add or extend keys in all locale files under src/messages/*.json (same keys every locale—no orphaned locales). IF application has LOCALES

Do not

Rely on root app/layout.tsx metadata alone for a route-specific SEO story.
Duplicate ad-hoc OG/twitter logic when buildOpenGraphAndTwitter already covers the case.
